NAME
     hubble - extrapolate particle positions in a box

SYNOPSIS
     drift _b_o_x-_n_u_m_b_e_r _p_a_r_t_i_c_l_e _d_e_l_t_a-_t

DESCRIPTION
     drift drifts the particles of  type  _p_a_r_t_i_c_l_e  in  box  _b_o_x-
     _n_u_m_b_e_r for _d_e_l_t_a-_t using the particle's velocity.  This com-
     mand is useful for interpolating between  time  frames  when
     making  movies.   To  move  particles  forward in time use a
     positive value for _d_e_l_t_a-_t and to move particles backward in
     time  use  a  negative value for _d_e_l_t_a-_t. NOTE: this command
     permanently changes the velocities of all the  particles  in
     box  _b_o_x-_n_u_m_b_e_r.  To undo a drift command repeat the command
     with a _d_e_l_t_a-_t of equal magnitude but of opposite sign.   If
     the box _b_o_x-_n_u_m_b_e_r is not loaded an error is generated.

OPTIONS
  Particle
     The possible choices for _p_a_r_t_i_c_l_e are:

          all
             Adjust the velocities of all the  particles  in  box
             _b_o_x-_n_u_m_b_e_r.

          baryon
             Adjust the velocities of all the gas and star parti-
             cles in box _b_o_x-_n_u_m_b_e_r.

          dark
             Adjust the velocities of only the dark matter parti-
             cles in box _b_o_x-_n_u_m_b_e_r

          gas
             Adjust the velocities of only the gas  particles  in
             box _b_o_x-_n_u_m_b_e_r.

          star
             Adjust the velocities of only the star particles  in
             box _b_o_x-_n_u_m_b_e_r.

